# Componentry contributor conventions

## Component + docs structure (must follow)

- **Component implementation**: `src/components/docs/registry/<slug>.tsx`
- **Preview/demo wrapper**: `src/components/docs/previews/<slug>-preview.tsx`
- **Docs page (layout + install + usage)**: `src/components/docs/<slug>.tsx`
- **Lazy docs importer map**: `src/components/docs/lazy-registry.ts` (add slug entry)
- **Site metadata**: `src/registry/index.ts` (add ComponentMetadata entry)
- **Shadcn registry index**: `public/registry.json` (add item)
- **Shadcn registry item JSON**: `public/r/<slug>.json` (must include file `content`)

## Shadcn registry item rules

- `public/r/<slug>.json` must follow schema `https://ui.shadcn.com/schema/registry-item.json`.
- Include `files[].content` for at least one file so the docs "View Source" and install tooling can work.
- Keep the first file as the main component file so `readComponentSource()` can display it.

## Media (Cloudinary) rules

- Store component media metadata (video URL, poster/thumbnail URL) in `src/registry/index.ts` under the component entry.
- Use env var `CLOUDINARY_URL` for base URL patterns when generating/deriving poster thumbnails.
- Do not hardcode secrets in repo. Only public URLs should be committed.

## OG images

- Component OG images are dynamic and generated in `src/app/docs/components/[slug]/opengraph-image.tsx`.
- Do not add per-component static OG PNGs unless there is a strong reason.

## When adding a new component

- Prefer using the generator script (see `scripts/` folder) instead of manual copy/paste.
- After scaffolding, update content (title/description, usage code, props table, preview).
- Ensure `npm run build` passes.

